shortDescription: The Porsche 918 Spyder is a mid-engine plug-in hybrid sports car manufactured by German automobile manufacturer Porsche.
LaFerrari, project name F150 (also unofficially referred to as the Ferrari LaFerrari or Ferrari F150), is a limited production hybrid sports car built by Italian automotive manufacturer Ferrari.
The Pagani Huayra, it’s the successor to the almighty Pagani Zonda and it’s named after a South American wind god called Huayra Tata.
The Bugatti Chiron is a mid-engine two-seater sports car developed and manufactured in Molsheim, France by French automobile manufacturer Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S..

The teardrop shape of the Ford GT is the result of extensive work in the wind tunnel. Its carbon-fiber body and its 647-horsepower 3.5L EcoBoost® V6 engine are the ultimate expressions of technological innovation.
The Ferrari 328 GTB and GTS (Type F106) are mid-engine V8, two seat sports cars produced by Italian automotive manufacturer Ferrari.
As a track-ready version of the Ford Mustang, the 2019 Shelby GT350 has even more muscular styling and next-level performance.
The Lamborghini Gallardo is a sports car built by the Italian automotive manufacturer Lamborghini from 2003 to 2013.

The Lamborghini Aventador SVJ represents an upgraded from previous Aventador models. Extensive use of carbon fiber in the aero package improves downforce and reduces drag while a titanium exhaust reduces overall weight.
The 2020 Dodge Charger is the modern take on an American classic.
The 1969 Dodge Charger is a classic example of the golden age of American muscle cars.
The newest mid-engine Corvette is the fastest model to date with head-turning looks we expect from a Corvette.

An American classic, the '57 Chevy.
The McLaren 720s is a supercar in its own right. Beautiful lines and breathtaking performance, this English speedster is without compromise.
The Rolls-Royce Phantom is the embodiment quiet, comfort and safety without compromise.
